Code solutions must adhere to senior-level best practices:
- Write clean, maintainable, and readable code
- Follow SOLID principles and design patterns
- Avoid hacks, workarounds, or temporary solutions
- Use proper error handling and validation
- Implement proper logging and monitoring
- Follow security best practices
- Write comprehensive tests
- Use proper dependency injection and inversion of control
- Document complex business logic and architectural decisions
